  "statement": "# Single Number\n\nEvery value appears twice except one. Return the single value.\n\n## Examples\n\n**Example 1**\n\n```text\nInput: nums = [2,2,1]\nOutput: 1\n```\n\n**Example 2**\n\n```text\nInput: nums = [4,1,2,1,2]\nOutput: 4\n```\n\n**Example 3**\n\n```text\nInput: nums = [-1]\nOutput: -1\n```\n\n## Constraints\n\n- Inputs are sized for local offline execution.\n- Return the value described by the method signature.",
  "editorial": "Use direct arithmetic, matrix indexing, or bit operations to preserve the required invariants while keeping extra state small.",
  "solution_notes": "```python\nclass Solution:\n    def singleNumber(self, nums):\n        out = 0\n        for value in nums: out ^= value\n        return out\n```",
